The national treasury has agreed not to introduce more taxes as recommended by the national assembly budgets and appropriations committee, as its drafts the 2021/22 financial year budget. appearing before, BAC, treasury CS was advised to consider increasing the tax base to accommodate more corporates in a bid to address the budget deficit. the committee lauded the treasury&rsquo;s move to borrow confessionally to meet the country&rsquo;s national budget.